---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'

const link = 'text-pink-500 underline underline-offset-2 transition-colors hover:text-pink-400'
---
<Base
  title="AudioSilo - Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for the AudioSilo self-hosted audiobook player."
>
  <div class="container py-14 sm:py-16">
    <div class="reveal mx-auto max-w-3xl text-body">
      <h1 class="mb-1 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight text-hi">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mb-8 text-dim">Last updated: 25 June 2026</p>

      <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        AudioSilo is a <strong class="text-hi">self-hosted audiobook player</strong>. The AudioSilo
        app is a <em>client</em> for an AudioSilo server that <strong class="text-hi">you</strong>
        (or whoever administers your server) run and control. In normal use, the app communicates
        <strong class="text-hi">only</strong> with the server address you provide, and the developer
        of AudioSilo operates
        <strong class="text-hi">no service that receives, stores, or processes your data</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">Who we are</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        AudioSilo ("the app") is published by <strong class="text-hi">KodeStar</strong>. Questions
        about this policy can be sent to
        <a class={link} href="mailto:kode@audiosilo.app">kode@audiosilo.app</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="my-8 rounded-xl border border-edge bg-surface p-6">
        <p class="mb-2 font-semibold text-hi">The short version</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
          <li>We do <strong class="text-hi">not</strong> collect, see, sell, or share your personal data.</li>
          <li>
            We use <strong class="text-hi">no</strong> analytics, advertising, tracking, or
            crash-reporting services.
          </li>
          <li>
            All of your content and account data lives on
            <strong class="text-hi">your own AudioSilo server</strong> and on
            <strong class="text-hi">your own device</strong>, not with us.
          </li>
          <li>The app contacts only the server <strong class="text-hi">you</strong> tell it to connect to.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">What information the app handles</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Because AudioSilo is self-hosted, almost everything stays between your device and the server
        you connect to.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-2 font-semibold text-hi">Stored on your device</p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
        <li>
          <strong class="text-hi">Your session token</strong>, kept in the operating system's
          encrypted secure storage (Keychain on iOS, Keystore on Android) so you stay signed in.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-hi">Downloaded audiobooks</strong>: audio files and cover art you
          choose to download for offline listening, stored in the app's private storage.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-hi">App preferences</strong>: settings such as playback speed, theme,
          and language, plus a local cache of your listening position.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-2 font-semibold text-hi">Sent to the server you choose</p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
        <li>
          When you sign in or pair, and as you listen, the app sends requests to the
          <strong class="text-hi">AudioSilo server address you provide</strong>. Your account
          credentials, listening progress, bookmarks, notes, and favourites are stored on
          <strong class="text-hi">that</strong> server, operated by you or your server's administrator.
        </li>
        <li>
          We (KodeStar) have <strong class="text-hi">no access</strong> to your server, your account,
          or any data on it.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        There is no central AudioSilo account system. Your account exists only on your self-hosted
        server.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">Device permissions</h2>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
        <li>
          <strong class="text-hi">Camera</strong>: used solely to scan a pairing QR code when
          connecting to your server. Images are processed on-device to read the code and are never
          stored or transmitted to us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-hi">Background audio</strong>: so playback continues when the app is
          backgrounded or the screen is locked.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-hi">Network access</strong>: to communicate with your AudioSilo server.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">Optional public demo</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        AudioSilo offers an optional, web-based public demo (at
        <span class="rounded border border-edge bg-raised px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm text-pink-300"
          >demo.audiosilo.app</span
        >) so people can try the player without setting up a server. The demo server creates a
        <strong class="text-hi">temporary, throwaway guest session</strong> with sample content; no
        personal account is created and demo data is ephemeral. Using the demo is optional and separate
        from connecting to your own server.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">Analytics, advertising, and tracking</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        AudioSilo contains <strong class="text-hi">no</strong> analytics, advertising, attribution, or
        third-party tracking software. We do not profile you and do not build advertising identifiers.
        Nothing about your usage is reported back to us.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">Third-party services</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        The app integrates no third-party data-collecting services. The only third parties involved
        are the <strong class="text-hi">app stores</strong> (Apple App Store, Google Play) that
        distribute the app, and the <strong class="text-hi">server you connect to</strong>, each
        governed by its own operator's terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">Data retention and deletion</h2>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
        <li>
          <strong class="text-hi">On your device:</strong> uninstalling the app removes its local
          data, including the stored session token, downloaded audiobooks, and preferences.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-hi">On your server:</strong> your account and listening data are
          retained according to your server's configuration. Because the server is under your control,
          you can delete your account and its data there at any time.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">Children's privacy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        AudioSilo is a general-audience audiobook player and is not directed at children under 13. We
        do not knowingly collect personal information from children; indeed, we collect personal
        information from no one.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">Security</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Communication between the app and your server uses standard transport security (HTTPS, which
        your server can be configured to enforce). Your session token is held in the device's
        encrypted secure storage. Because we hold no user data centrally, there is no central store of
        your information to be breached.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        We may update this policy as the app evolves. Material changes will be reflected by the "Last
        updated" date above and published at the same URL.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mb-3 mt-10 text-2xl font-bold text-pink-400">Contact</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Questions about this privacy policy can be sent to
        <a class={link} href="mailto:kode@audiosilo.app">kode@audiosilo.app</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
